The commander of Airborne Forces (VDV) Gen-Col Andrei Serdyukov and commander of the Southern Group of Forces (SGF) general of the army Alexandr Dvornikov are among the top Russian army figures to be removed from their jobs as a result of a Kremlin shake-up, the UK's Ministry of Defence said in Saturday's war update. While the firings suggest dissatisfaction in Moscow over seemingly insufficient territorial advances, reports from the battlefield point to a stark reality for Ukrainians fighting to defend their country, as troops were forced to withdraw on Friday from the strongly-disputed city of Severodonetsk in Luhansk, which is part of the eastern Donbas region that Putin has made an "unconditional priority" in his invasion goals. FOLLOW BELOW FOR LIVE UPDATES ON THE WAR IN UKRAINE